#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="mn41"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn41:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 41 "
msgstr "Middle Discourses 41 "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn41:0.2"
msgid "Sāleyyakasutta "
msgstr "The People of Sālā "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: nya1, pts-vp-pli1.285, sc1
msgctxt "mn41:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "mn41:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kosalesu cārikaṃ caramāno mahatā bhikkhusaṅghena saddhiṃ yena sālā nāma kosalānaṃ brāhmaṇagāmo tadavasari. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was wandering in the land of the Kosalans together with a large Saṅgha of mendicants when he arrived at a village of the Kosalan brahmins named Sālā. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya2
msgctxt "mn41:2.1"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho sāleyyakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā: "
msgstr "The brahmins and householders of Sālā heard, "

msgctxt "mn41:2.2"
msgid "“samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo sakyaputto sakyakulā pabbajito kosalesu cārikaṃ caramāno mahatā bhikkhusaṅghena saddhiṃ sālaṃ anuppatto. "
msgstr "“It seems the ascetic Gotama—a Sakyan, gone forth from a Sakyan family—while wandering in the land of the Kosalans has arrived at Sālā, together with a large Saṅgha of mendicants. "

msgctxt "mn41:2.3"
msgid "Taṃ kho pana bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ evaṃ kalyāṇo kittisaddo abbhuggato: "
msgstr "He has this good reputation: "

msgctxt "mn41:2.4"
msgid "‘itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’. "
msgstr "‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’ "

msgctxt "mn41:2.5"
msgid "So imaṃ lokaṃ sadevakaṃ samārakaṃ sabrahmakaṃ sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiṃ pajaṃ sadevamanussaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedeti. "
msgstr "He has realized with his own insight this world—with its gods, Māras and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, gods and humans—and he makes it known to others. "

msgctxt "mn41:2.6"
msgid "So dhammaṃ deseti ādikalyāṇaṃ majjhekalyāṇaṃ pariyosānakalyāṇaṃ sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ; "
msgstr "He proclaims a teaching that is good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, with the right meaning and phrasing. "

msgctxt "mn41:2.7"
msgid "kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pakāseti. "
msgstr "He reveals an entirely full and pure spiritual life. "

msgctxt "mn41:2.8"
msgid "Sādhu kho pana tathārūpānaṃ arahataṃ dassanaṃ hotī”ti. "
msgstr "It’s good to see such perfected ones.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya3, sc2
msgctxt "mn41:3.1"
msgid "Atha kho sāleyyakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā appekacce bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu; appekacce bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodiṃsu, sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu; appekacce yena bhagavā tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu; appekacce bhagavato santike nāmagottaṃ sāvetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu; appekacce tuṇhībhūtā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho sāleyyakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "Then the brahmins and householders of Sālā went up to the Buddha. Before sitting down to one side, some bowed, some exchanged greetings and polite conversation, some held up their joined palms toward the Buddha, some announced their name and clan, while some kept silent. Seated to one side they said to the Buddha: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
	#. REF: nya4
msgctxt "mn41:3.2"
msgid "“ko nu kho, bho gotama, hetu, ko paccayo, yena m’idhekacce sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjanti? "
msgstr "“What is the cause, Master Gotama, what is the reason why some sentient beings, when their body breaks up, after death, are reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell? "

msgctxt "mn41:3.3"
msgid "Ko pana, bho gotama, hetu, ko paccayo, yena m’idhekacce sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjantī”ti? "
msgstr "And what is the cause, Master Gotama, what is the reason why some sentient beings, when their body breaks up, after death, are reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya5, pts-vp-pli1.286, sc3
msgctxt "mn41:5.1"
msgid "“Adhammacariyāvisamacariyāhetu kho, gahapatayo, evam’idhekacce sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjanti. "
msgstr "“Unprincipled and immoral conduct is the reason why some sentient beings, when their body breaks up, after death, are reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell. "

msgctxt "mn41:5.2"
msgid "Dhammacariyāsamacariyāhetu kho, gahapatayo, evam’idhekacce sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjantī”ti. "
msgstr "Principled and moral conduct is the reason why some sentient beings, when their body breaks up, after death, are reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya6, sc4
msgctxt "mn41:6.1"
msgid "“Na kho mayaṃ imassa bhoto gotamassa saṅkhittena bhāsitassa, vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa, vitthārena atthaṃ ājānāma. "
msgstr "“We don’t understand the detailed meaning of Master Gotama’s brief statement. "

msgctxt "mn41:6.2"
msgid "Sādhu no bhavaṃ gotamo tathā dhammaṃ desetu, yathā mayaṃ imassa bhoto gotamassa saṅkhittena bhāsitassa, vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa, vitthārena atthaṃ ājāneyyāmā”ti. "
msgstr "Master Gotama, please teach us this matter in detail so we can understand the meaning.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn41:6.3"
msgid "“Tena hi, gahapatayo, suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti. "
msgstr "“Well then, householders, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn41:6.4"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bho”ti kho sāleyyakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā bhagavato paccassosuṃ. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” they replied. "

msgctxt "mn41:6.5"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "The Buddha said this: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya7, sc5
msgctxt "mn41:7.1"
msgid "“Tividhaṃ kho, gahapatayo, kāyena adhammacariyāvisamacariyā hoti, catubbidhaṃ vācāya adhammacariyāvisamacariyā hoti, tividhaṃ manasā adhammacariyāvisamacariyā hoti. "
msgstr "“Householders, unprincipled and immoral conduct is threefold by way of body, fourfold by way of speech, and threefold by way of mind. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya8, sc6
msgctxt "mn41:8.1"
msgid "Kathañca, gahapatayo, tividhaṃ kāyena adhammacariyāvisamacariyā hoti? "
msgstr "And how is unprincipled and immoral conduct threefold by way of body? "

#. VAR: luddo → luddo dāruṇo (mr)
#. VAR: adayāpanno pāṇabhūtesu → sab­bapāṇa­bhū­tesu (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "mn41:8.2"
msgid "Idha, gahapatayo, ekacco pāṇātipātī hoti, luddo lohitapāṇi hatappahate niviṭṭho adayāpanno pāṇabhūtesu. "
msgstr "It’s when a certain person kills living creatures. They’re violent, bloody-handed, a hardened killer, merciless to living beings. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "mn41:8.3"
msgid "Adinnādāyī kho pana hoti. Yaṃ taṃ parassa paravittūpakaraṇaṃ, gāmagataṃ vā araññagataṃ vā, taṃ adinnaṃ theyyasaṅkhātaṃ ādātā hoti. "
msgstr "They steal. With the intention to commit theft, they take the wealth or belongings of others from village or wilderness. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "mn41:8.4"
msgid "Kāmesumicchācārī kho pana hoti. Yā tā māturakkhitā piturakkhitā mātāpiturakkhitā bhāturakkhitā bhaginirakkhitā ñātirakkhitā gottarakkhitā dhammarakkhitā sassāmikā saparidaṇḍā antamaso mālāguḷaparikkhittāpi, tathārūpāsu cārittaṃ āpajjitā hoti. "
msgstr "They commit sexual misconduct. They have sexual relations with women who have their mother, father, both mother and father, brother, sister, relatives, or clan as guardian. They have sexual relations with a woman who is protected on principle, or who has a husband, or whose violation is punishable by law, or even one who has been garlanded as a token of betrothal. "

msgctxt "mn41:8.5"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, gahapatayo, tividhaṃ kāyena adhammacariyāvisamacariyā hoti. "
msgstr "This is how unprincipled and immoral conduct is threefold by way of body. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya9, sc9
msgctxt "mn41:9.1"
msgid "Kathañca, gahapatayo, catubbidhaṃ vācāya adhammacariyāvisamacariyā hoti? "
msgstr "And how is unprincipled and immoral conduct fourfold by way of speech? "

msgctxt "mn41:9.2"
msgid "Idha, gahapatayo, ekacco musāvādī hoti. Sabhāgato vā parisāgato vā, ñātimajjhagato vā pūgamajjhagato vā rājakulamajjhagato vā, abhinīto sakkhipuṭṭho: ‘ehambho purisa, yaṃ jānāsi taṃ vadehī’ti, so ajānaṃ vā āha: ‘jānāmī’ti, jānaṃ vā āha: na jānāmī’ti, ‘apassaṃ vā āha: ‘passāmī’ti, passaṃ vā āha: ‘na passāmī’ti. Iti attahetu vā parahetu vā āmisakiñcikkhahetu vā sampajānamusā bhāsitā hoti. "
msgstr "It’s when a certain person lies. They’re summoned to a council, an assembly, a family meeting, a guild, or to the royal court, and asked to bear witness: ‘Please, mister, say what you know.’ Not knowing, they say ‘I know.’ Knowing, they say ‘I don’t know.’ Not seeing, they say ‘I see.’ And seeing, they say ‘I don’t see.’ So they deliberately lie for the sake of themselves or another, or for some trivial worldly reason. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
#. VAR: bhettā → bhedetā (s1-3, km) | bhedakā (mr)
msgctxt "mn41:9.3"
msgid "Pisuṇavāco kho pana hoti. Ito sutvā amutra akkhātā imesaṃ bhedāya, amutra vā sutvā imesaṃ akkhātā amūsaṃ bhedāya. Iti samaggānaṃ vā bhettā, bhinnānaṃ vā anuppadātā, vaggārāmo vaggarato vagganandī vaggakaraṇiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti. "
msgstr "They speak divisively. They repeat in one place what they heard in another so as to divide people against each other. And so they divide those who are harmonious, supporting division, delighting in division, loving division, speaking words that promote division. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.287, sc11
#. VAR: aṇḍakā → kaṇḍakā (mr)
msgctxt "mn41:9.4"
msgid "Pharusavāco kho pana hoti. Yā sā vācā aṇḍakā kakkasā parakaṭukā parābhisajjanī kodhasāmantā asamādhisaṃvattanikā, tathārūpiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti. "
msgstr "They speak harshly. They use the kinds of words that are cruel, nasty, hurtful, offensive, bordering on anger, not leading to immersion. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "mn41:9.5"
msgid "Samphappalāpī kho pana hoti. Akālavādī abhūtavādī anatthavādī adhammavādī avinayavādī. Anidhānavatiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti akālena anapadesaṃ apariyantavatiṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ. "
msgstr "They talk nonsense. Their speech is untimely, and is neither factual nor beneficial. It has nothing to do with the teaching or the training. Their words have no value, and are untimely, unreasonable, rambling, and pointless. "

msgctxt "mn41:9.6"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, gahapatayo, catubbidhaṃ vācāya adhammacariyāvisamacariyā hoti. "
msgstr "This is how unprincipled and immoral conduct is fourfold by way of speech. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya10, sc13
msgctxt "mn41:10.1"
msgid "Kathañca, gahapatayo, tividhaṃ manasā adhammacariyāvisamacariyā hoti? "
msgstr "And how is unprincipled and immoral conduct threefold by way of mind? "

msgctxt "mn41:10.2"
msgid "Idha, gahapatayo, ekacco abhijjhālu hoti, yaṃ taṃ parassa paravittūpakaraṇaṃ taṃ abhijjhātā hoti: ‘aho vata yaṃ parassa taṃ mamassā’ti. "
msgstr "It's when a certain person is covetous. They covet the wealth and belongings of others: ‘Oh, if only their belongings were mine!’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc14
#. VAR: ahesun’ti → mā vā ahesuṃ iti vāti (bj, pts1, mr)
#. VAR: vinassantu vā → etthantare pāṭho syā1-3 potthakesu
msgctxt "mn41:10.3"
msgid "Byāpannacitto kho pana hoti paduṭṭhamanasaṅkappo: ‘ime sattā haññantu vā vajjhantu vā ucchijjantu vā vinassantu vā mā vā ahesun’ti. "
msgstr "They have ill will and hateful intentions: ‘May these sentient beings be killed, slaughtered, slain, destroyed, or annihilated!’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc15
msgctxt "mn41:10.4"
msgid "Micchādiṭṭhiko kho pana hoti viparītadassano: "
msgstr "They have wrong view. Their perspective is distorted: "

msgctxt "mn41:10.5"
msgid "‘natthi dinnaṃ natthi yiṭṭhaṃ natthi hutaṃ, natthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko, natthi ayaṃ loko natthi paro loko, natthi mātā natthi pitā, natthi sattā opapātikā, natthi loke samaṇabrāhmaṇā sammaggatā sammāpaṭipannā ye imañca lokaṃ parañca lokaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedentī’ti. "
msgstr "‘There’s no meaning in giving, sacrifice, or offerings. There’s no fruit or result of good and bad deeds. There’s no afterlife. There’s no obligation to mother and father. No beings are reborn spontaneously. And there’s no ascetic or brahmin who is well attained and practiced, and who describes the afterlife after realizing it with their own insight.’ "

msgctxt "mn41:10.6"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, gahapatayo, tividhaṃ manasā adhammacariyāvisamacariyā hoti. "
msgstr "This is how unprincipled and immoral conduct is threefold by way of mind. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc16
msgctxt "mn41:10.7"
msgid "Evaṃ adhammacariyāvisamacariyāhetu kho, gahapatayo, evam’idhekacce sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjanti. "
msgstr "That’s how unprincipled and immoral conduct is the reason why some sentient beings, when their body breaks up, after death, are reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya11, sc17
msgctxt "mn41:11.1"
msgid "Tividhaṃ kho, gahapatayo, kāyena dhammacariyāsamacariyā hoti, catubbidhaṃ vācāya dhammacariyāsamacariyā hoti, tividhaṃ manasā dhammacariyāsamacariyā hoti. "
msgstr "Householders, principled and moral conduct is threefold by way of body, fourfold by way of speech, and threefold by way of mind. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya12, sc18
msgctxt "mn41:12.1"
msgid "Kathañca, gahapatayo, tividhaṃ kāyena dhammacariyāsamacariyā hoti? "
msgstr "And how is principled and moral conduct threefold by way of body? "

msgctxt "mn41:12.2"
msgid "Idha, gahapatayo, ekacco pāṇātipātaṃ pahāya pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, nihitadaṇḍo nihitasattho lajjī dayāpanno sabbapāṇabhūtahitānukampī viharati. "
msgstr "It’s when a certain person gives up killing living creatures. They renounce the rod and the sword. They’re scrupulous and kind, living full of compassion for all living beings. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc19
msgctxt "mn41:12.3"
msgid "Adinnādānaṃ pahāya adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti. Yaṃ taṃ parassa paravittūpakaraṇaṃ, gāmagataṃ vā araññagataṃ vā, taṃ nādinnaṃ theyyasaṅkhātaṃ ādātā hoti. "
msgstr "They give up stealing. They don’t, with the intention to commit theft, take the wealth or belongings of others from village or wilderness. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.288, sc20
msgctxt "mn41:12.4"
msgid "Kāmesumicchācāraṃ pahāya kāmesumicchācārā paṭivirato hoti. Yā tā māturakkhitā piturakkhitā mātāpiturakkhitā bhāturakkhitā bhaginirakkhitā ñātirakkhitā gottarakkhitā dhammarakkhitā sassāmikā saparidaṇḍā antamaso mālāguḷaparikkhittāpi, tathārūpāsu na cārittaṃ āpajjitā hoti. "
msgstr "They give up sexual misconduct. They don’t have sexual relations with women who have their mother, father, both mother and father, brother, sister, relatives, or clan as guardian. They don’t have sexual relations with a woman who is protected on principle, or who has a husband, or whose violation is punishable by law, or even one who has been garlanded as a token of betrothal. "

msgctxt "mn41:12.5"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, gahapatayo, tividhaṃ kāyena dhammacariyāsamacariyā hoti. "
msgstr "This is how principled and moral conduct is threefold by way of body. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya13, sc21
msgctxt "mn41:13.1"
msgid "Kathañca, gahapatayo, catubbidhaṃ vācāya dhammacariyāsamacariyā hoti? "
msgstr "And how is principled and moral conduct fourfold by way of speech? "

msgctxt "mn41:13.2"
msgid "Idha, gahapatayo, ekacco musāvādaṃ pahāya musāvādā paṭivirato hoti. Sabhāgato vā parisāgato vā, ñātimajjhagato vā pūgamajjhagato vā rājakulamajjhagato vā, abhinīto sakkhipuṭṭho: ‘ehambho purisa, yaṃ jānāsi taṃ vadehī’ti, so ajānaṃ vā āha: ‘na jānāmī’ti, jānaṃ vā āha: ‘jānāmī’ti, apassaṃ vā āha: ‘na passāmī’ti, passaṃ vā āha: ‘passāmī’ti. Iti attahetu vā parahetu vā āmisakiñcikkhahetu vā na sampajānamusā bhāsitā hoti. "
msgstr "It’s when a certain person gives up lying. They’re summoned to a council, an assembly, a family meeting, a guild, or to the royal court, and asked to bear witness: ‘Please, mister, say what you know.’ Not knowing, they say ‘I don’t know.’ Knowing, they say ‘I know.’ Not seeing, they say ‘I don’t see.’ And seeing, they say ‘I see.’ So they don’t deliberately lie for the sake of themselves or another, or for some trivial worldly reason. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc22
msgctxt "mn41:13.3"
msgid "Pisuṇaṃ vācaṃ pahāya pisuṇāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti, ito sutvā na amutra akkhātā imesaṃ bhedāya, amutra vā sutvā na imesaṃ akkhātā amūsaṃ bhedāya. Iti bhinnānaṃ vā sandhātā, sahitānaṃ vā anuppadātā, samaggārāmo samaggarato samagganandī samaggakaraṇiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti. "
msgstr "They give up divisive speech. They don’t repeat in one place what they heard in another so as to divide people against each other. Instead, they reconcile those who are divided, supporting unity, delighting in harmony, loving harmony, speaking words that promote harmony. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc23
msgctxt "mn41:13.4"
msgid "Pharusaṃ vācaṃ pahāya pharusāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti. Yā sā vācā nelā kaṇṇasukhā pemanīyā hadayaṅgamā porī bahujanakantā bahujanamanāpā—tathārūpiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti. "
msgstr "They give up harsh speech. They speak in a way that’s mellow, pleasing to the ear, lovely, going to the heart, polite, likable, and agreeable to the people. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc24
msgctxt "mn41:13.5"
msgid "Samphappalāpaṃ pahāya samphappalāpā paṭivirato hoti. Kālavādī bhūtavādī atthavādī dhammavādī vinayavādī nidhānavatiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti kālena sāpadesaṃ pariyantavatiṃ atthasaṃhitaṃ. "
msgstr "They give up talking nonsense. Their words are timely, true, and meaningful, in line with the teaching and training. They say things at the right time which are valuable, reasonable, succinct, and beneficial. "

msgctxt "mn41:13.6"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, gahapatayo, catubbidhaṃ vācāya dhammacariyāsamacariyā hoti. "
msgstr "This is how principled and moral conduct is fourfold by way of speech. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya14, sc25
msgctxt "mn41:14.1"
msgid "Kathañca, gahapatayo, tividhaṃ manasā dhammacariyāsamacariyā hoti? "
msgstr "And how is principled and moral conduct threefold by way of mind? "

msgctxt "mn41:14.2"
msgid "Idha, gahapatayo, ekacco anabhijjhālu hoti, yaṃ taṃ parassa paravittūpakaraṇaṃ taṃ nābhijjhātā hoti: ‘aho vata yaṃ parassa taṃ mamassā’ti. "
msgstr "It's when a certain person is not covetous. They don’t covet the wealth and belongings of others: ‘Oh, if only their belongings were mine!’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc26
msgctxt "mn41:14.3"
msgid "Abyāpannacitto kho pana hoti appaduṭṭhamanasaṅkappo: ‘ime sattā averā abyābajjhā anīghā sukhī attānaṃ pariharantū’ti. "
msgstr "They have a kind heart and loving intentions: ‘May these sentient beings live free of enmity and ill will, untroubled and happy!’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc27
msgctxt "mn41:14.4"
msgid "Sammādiṭṭhiko kho pana hoti aviparītadassano: "
msgstr "They have right view, an undistorted perspective: "

msgctxt "mn41:14.5"
msgid "‘atthi dinnaṃ atthi yiṭṭhaṃ atthi hutaṃ, atthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko, atthi ayaṃ loko atthi paro loko, atthi mātā atthi pitā, atthi sattā opapātikā, atthi loke samaṇabrāhmaṇā sammaggatā sammāpaṭipannā ye imañca lokaṃ parañca lokaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedentī’ti. "
msgstr "‘There is meaning in giving, sacrifice, and offerings. There are fruits and results of good and bad deeds. There is an afterlife. There is obligation to mother and father. There are beings reborn spontaneously. And there are ascetics and brahmins who are well attained and practiced, and who describe the afterlife after realizing it with their own insight.’ "

msgctxt "mn41:14.6"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, gahapatayo, tividhaṃ manasā dhammacariyāsamacariyā hoti. "
msgstr "This is how principled and moral conduct is threefold by way of mind. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc28
msgctxt "mn41:14.7"
msgid "Evaṃ dhammacariyāsamacariyāhetu kho, gahapatayo, evam’idhekacce sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjanti. "
msgstr "This is how principled and moral conduct is the reason why some sentient beings, when their body breaks up, after death, are reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya15, pts-vp-pli1.289, sc29
msgctxt "mn41:15.1"
msgid "Ākaṅkheyya ce, gahapatayo, dhammacārī samacārī: "
msgstr "A person of principled and moral conduct might wish: "

msgctxt "mn41:15.2"
msgid "‘aho vatāhaṃ kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā khattiyamahāsālānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjeyyan’ti; "
msgstr "‘If only, when my body breaks up, after death, I would be reborn in the company of well-to-do aristocrats!’ "

msgctxt "mn41:15.3"
msgid "ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ vijjati, yaṃ so kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā khattiyamahāsālānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjeyya. "
msgstr "It’s possible that this might happen. "

msgctxt "mn41:15.4"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "mn41:15.5"
msgid "Tathā hi so dhammacārī samacārī. "
msgstr "Because they have principled and moral conduct. "

