msgstr "Because they have principled and moral conduct.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya44, pts-vp-pli1.290, sc36
msgctxt "mn41:44.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, sāleyyakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "When he had spoken, the brahmins and householders of Sālā said to the Buddha, "

msgctxt "mn41:44.2"
msgid "“abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama, abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama. "
msgstr "“Excellent, Master Gotama! Excellent! "

msgctxt "mn41:44.3"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bho gotama, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā vivareyya, mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya: ‘cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti; evamevaṃ bhotā gotamena anekapariyāyena dhammo pakāsito. "
msgstr "As if he were righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark so people with good eyes can see what’s there, Master Gotama has made the teaching clear in many ways. "

msgctxt "mn41:44.4"
msgid "Ete mayaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāma dhammañca bhikkhusaṃghañca. "
msgstr "We go for refuge to Master Gotama, to the teaching, and to the mendicant Saṅgha. "

#. VAR: pāṇupete → pāṇupetaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "mn41:44.5"
msgid "Upāsake no bhavaṃ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupete saraṇaṃ gate”ti. "
msgstr "From this day forth, may Master Gotama remember us as lay followers who have gone for refuge for life.” "

